President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Texas and ordered Federal assistance to support recovery efforts in areas affected by Hurricane Laura from August 23 to August 27, 2020. The declaration makes federal funding available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The counties of Galveston, Jasper, Jefferson, Newton, and Orange are eligible for this assistance. Jerry S. Thomas has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.